oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Civil War ambrotype [Willett?]
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Photographer J.W. Keen, Jonesboro, TN
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Cased ambrotype of four people, one in Confederate uniform. Possibly Z.T. (Zaddock T.) Willett or T.H. Walker, based on newspaper clipping that accompanied the ambrotype. The other man is holding a Confederate uniform cap. Two unidentified women. Gold highlights and light hand tinting. One break at left. Taken by photographer J.W. Keen, Jonesboro, TN, October 14, 1861.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Group portraits; Civil wars; Military uniforms; Ambrotypes;
